  "prompt": "What are some relationship hacks that actually are worth learning?",
  "response": "Here are some relationship \"hacks\" that can be genuinely helpful:\n\n1. Active listening\n- Actually pay attention when your partner speaks\n- Reflect back what you've heard\n- Ask clarifying questions\n\n2. Regular communication\n- Set aside dedicated time to talk\n- Discuss both small and big issues\n- Be honest and transparent\n\n3. Practice empathy\n- Try to understand your partner's perspective\n- Validate their feelings\n- Show you're listening without judgment\n\n4. Learn each other's love languages\n- Understand how your partner gives/receives love\n- Adjust your approach accordingly\n\n5. Maintain individual identities\n- Keep personal hobbies and friendships\n- Support each other's individual growth\n- Don't become overly dependent\n\n6. Regular appreciation\n- Express gratitude for small things\n- Compliment each other\n- Acknowledge efforts\n\n7. Conflict resolution skills\n- Use \"I\" statements\n- Stay calm\n- Focus on solving the problem, not winning\n\n8. Physical and emotional intimacy\n- Regular affection\n- Non-sexual touch\n- Emotional vulnerability\n\n9. Shared experiences\n- Try new activities together\n- Create mutual memories\n- Plan date nights\n\n10. Continuous learning about each other\n- Ask questions\n- Stay curious\n- Avoid assumptions",
